ction\nof dust grown in the interstellar medium ($<$10$\\%$). Our results provide an\nalternative for the chemical evolution models that require extremely low\nsupernova dust production efficiencies and short grain growth timescales to\nreproduce local scaling laws, and could help solving the conundrum on whether\nor not grains can grow efficiently in the interstellar medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 18:15:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-04"}
