muting unitaries $u_0$. We obtain the bounds \\[ 2\\sqrt{1-\\frac{1}{d}}\\leq\nc(u_f,u_0)\\leq 2\\sqrt{1-\\frac{1}{2d}}. \\] From this, we recover Passer's upper\nbound for the universal unitaries $c({\\mathrm u},u_0)\\leq\\sqrt{2d}$. In the\ncase $d=3$ we obtain the new lower bound $c({\\mathrm u},u_0)\\geq 1.858$\nimproving on the previously known lower bound $c({\\mathrm u},u_0)\\geq\\sqrt{3}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 18:36:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Jun 2020 16:12:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 23 Jun 2021 11:54:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-09"}
