{"id":"2006.01872","submitter":"J. Harnad","authors":"J. Harnad and B. Runov","title":"Constellations and $\\tau$-functions for rationally weighted Hurwitz\n  numbers","comments":"37 pages. Added remark 2.7. Corrected eqs. (4.10) and (4.17).\n  Corrected several notational inconsistencies and added missing reference\n  citations","journal-ref":"Ann. Inst. H. Poincar\\'e D 8, 119-158 (2021)","doi":"10.4171/AIHPD/104","report-no":null,"categories":"math-ph hep-th math.CO math.GR math.MP nlin.SI","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Weighted constellations give graphical representations of weighted branched\ncoverings of the Riemann sphere. They were introduced to provide a\ncombinatorial interpretation of the $2$D Toda $\\tau$-functions of\nhypergeometric type serving as generating functions for weighted Hurwitz\nnumbers in the case of polynomial weight generating functions. The product over\nall vertex and edge weights of a given weighted constellation, summed over all\nconfigurations, reproduces the $\\tau$-function. In the present work, this is\ngeneralized to constellations in which the weighting parameters are determined\nby a rational weight generating function. The associated $\\tau$-function may be\nexpressed as a sum over the weights of doubly labelled weighted constellations,\nwith two types of weighting parameters associated to each equivalence class of\nbranched coverings. The double labelling of branch points, referred to as\n\"colour\" and \"flavour\" indices, is required by the fact that, in the Taylor\nexpansion of the weight generating function, a particular colour from amongst\nthe denominator parameters may appear multiply, and the flavour labels indicate\nthis multiplicity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 18:42:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 6 Jun 2020 22:40:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2020 01:44:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
